The AAA method:
 - Arrange the variables your test requires
 - Act on the methods your test requires
 - Assert a comparison of the expected and actual values that will prove the code works

 Example:
 @Test
 public void addReturnsCorrectSum() {
 // Arrange
 Arithmetic adder = new Arithmetic();
 int n1 = 3;
 int n2 = 5;
 // Act
 int actualSum = adder.add(n1, n2);
 // Assert
 assertEquals(expectedSum, actualSum);

 Assertion Methods
  - assertEquals() when you expect the two values to be equal
  - assertTrue() when you expect a conditional expression to eval to true
  - assertFalse() when you expect a conditional expression to eval to false
  - assertNotNull() when you expect the value of some piece of data to be null